{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879307714,"sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7ae5e001z12Nj0W1ZYpmfL","messageID":"msg_d7aa79331001xlSKjBm34B1DTW","sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-017\n2: title: PicoD JWT 中间件\n3: module: pkg/picod\n4: language: Go\n5: size: S\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件\n9: # Module: pkg/picod\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: S\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: picod-jwt-middleware\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for PicoD that\n23:     validates bearer tokens on incoming API requests. The middleware provides\n24:     secure access control to PicoD command execution endpoints by verifying\n25:     token signatures, expiration, and issuer claims.\n26: \n27: # Scope\n28: scope:\n29:   in:\n30:     - JWT middleware for HTTP/gRPC request validation\n31:     - Token signature verification (HS256, RS256 algorithms)\n32:     - Token expiration and issuer claim validation\n33:     - Middleware injection into PicoD API handlers\n34:     - Configuration for JWT keys and validation rules\n35:     - Error handling for invalid/missing tokens\n36:   out:\n37:     - Full OAuth2/OIDC flow implementation\n38:     - Token refresh mechanism\n39:     - Authorization scope enforcement (RBAC)\n40:     - Session management\n41:     - Token generation/issuance\n42: \n43: # Acceptance Criteria\n44: acceptance:\n45:   - JWT middleware validates bearer tokens on requests\n46:   - Support for HS256 and RS256 signing algorithms\n47:   - Token expiration validation with configurable clock skew\n48:   - Issuer claim validation\n49:   - Proper error responses for authentication failures\n50:   - Middleware can be applied to specific routes/endpoints\n51:   - Configuration via environment variables\n52:   - Unit tests for validation logic\n53:   - Integration tests with mock JWT provider\n54: \n55: # References\n56: references:\n57:   - AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API\n58:   - RFC 7519: JSON Web Token (JWT)\n59: \n60: # Estimation\n61: estimation:\n62:   size: S\n63:   story_points: 2\n64:   days: 2\n\n(End of file - total 64 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-017\ntitle: PicoD JWT 中间件\nmodule: pkg/picod\nlanguage: Go\nsize: S\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件\n# Module: pkg/picod\n# Language: Go\n# Size: S\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: picod-jwt-middleware","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775879307688,"end":1775879307712}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879307716,"sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7a7ec001c3VcfvhP16ssDc","messageID":"msg_d7aa79331001xlSKjBm34B1DTW","sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 (PicoD JWT Middleware)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** S  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-1 (Kickoff) → ST-2 (Design)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-017 implements JWT authentication middleware for PicoD API endpoints. The middleware validates bearer tokens using HMAC (HS256) or RSA (RS256) signatures, with support for expiration and issuer claim validation.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-2.1 — Type Definitions\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 2.1.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n22: | 2.1.2 | Define `Claims` struct (Subject, Issuer, ExpiresAt, IssuedAt) | All fields present with JSON tags | 0.5h |\n23: | 2.1.3 | Define `ValidationOptions` struct | Algorithm, Secret/PublicKey, ExpectedIssuer, ClockSkew fields | 0.5h |\n24: | 2.1.4 | Define `MiddlewareOptions` struct | Validator and ErrorHandler fields | 0.5h |\n25: \n26: **Deliverable:** Type definitions compile and match delta-spec.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## ST-2.2 — Error Definitions\n31: \n32: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n33: |---|------|--------------|------|\n34: | 2.2.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n35: | 2.2.2 | Define `ErrMissingToken` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n36: | 2.2.3 | Define `ErrInvalidTokenFormat` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n37: | 2.2.4 | Define `ErrInvalidSignature` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n38: | 2.2.5 | Define `ErrTokenExpired` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n39: | 2.2.6 | Define `ErrInvalidIssuer` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n40: | 2.2.7 | Define `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n41: \n42: **Deliverable:** All error types defined and exportable.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## ST-2.3 — Token Validation\n47: \n48: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n49: |---|------|--------------|------|\n50: | 2.3.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n51: | 2.3.2 | Define `JWTValidator` interface with ValidateToken method | Interface signature matches spec | 0.5h |\n52: | 2.3.3 | Implement `NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)` | Returns initialized validator | 0.5h |\n53: | 2.3.4 | Implement HS256 signature verification | Valid token passes, invalid fails | 1h |\n54: | 2.3.5 | Implement RS256 signature verification | Valid token passes, invalid fails | 1h |\n55: | 2.3.6 | Implement token parsing with claims extraction | Claims extracted correctly | 0.5h |\n56: | 2.3.7 | Implement expiration validation with clock skew | Expired tokens rejected, skew applied | 0.5h |\n57: | 2.3.8 | Implement issuer claim validation | Wrong issuer returns error | 0.5h |\n58: | 2.3.9 | Implement algorithm validation | Unsupported alg rejected | 0.5h |\n59: \n60: **Deliverable:** Validator implementation with all algorithms.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## ST-2.4 — HTTP Middleware\n65: \n66: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n67: |---|------|--------------|------|\n68: | 2.4.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n69: | 2.4.2 | Implement `JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler` | Returns middleware function | 0.5h |\n70: | 2.4.3 | Implement bearer token extraction from Authorization header | Token extracted correctly | 0.5h |\n71: | 2.4.4 | Implement error handling with standardized responses | JSON error responses match spec | 0.5h |\n72: | 2.4.5 | Implement claims injection into request context | GetClaims retrieves claims | 0.5h |\n73: | 2.4.6 | Implement `GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)` helper | Returns claims if present | 0.5h |\n74: \n75: **Deliverable:** Middleware function that validates tokens on HTTP requests.\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## ST-2.5 — Configuration\n80: \n81: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n82: |---|------|--------------|------|\n83: | 2.5.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n84: | 2.5.2 | Implement `LoadConfigFromEnv() (*ValidationOptions, error)` | Reads all env vars | 0.5h |\n85: | 2.5.3 | Support PICOD_JWT_SECRET for HS256 | Secret loaded correctly | 0.5h |\n86: | 2.5.4 | Support PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY for RS256 | Key file loaded and parsed | 0.5h |\n87: | 2.5.5 | Support PICOD_JWT_ISSUER (required) | Error if missing | 0.5h |\n88: | 2.5.6 | Support PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW parsing | Duration parsed correctly | 0.5h |\n89: | 2.5.7 | Support PICOD_JWT_ALG selection | Algorithm selected correctly | 0.5h |\n90: \n91: **Deliverable:** Configuration loading from environment.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## ST-2.6 — Unit Tests (Validator)\n96: \n97: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n98: |---|------|--------------|------|\n99: | 2.6.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | File compiles with build tag | 0.5h |\n100: | 2.6.2 | Write `TestValidateToken_HS256_Success` | Valid token passes | 0.5h |\n101: | 2.6.3 | Write `TestValidateToken_HS256_InvalidSignature` | Wrong secret fails | 0.5h |\n102: | 2.6.4 | Write `TestValidateToken_RS256_Success` | Valid RSA token passes | 0.5h |\n103: | 2.6.5 | Write `TestValidateToken_RS256_InvalidSignature` | Wrong key fails | 0.5h |\n104: | 2.6.6 | Write `TestValidateToken_Expired` | Expired token rejected | 0.5h |\n105: | 2.6.7 | Write `TestValidateToken_ClockSkew` | Skew tolerance applied | 0.5h |\n106: | 2.6.8 | Write `TestValidateToken_InvalidIssuer` | Wrong issuer rejected | 0.5h |\n107: | 2.6.9 | Write `TestValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm` | ES256 rejected if not allowed | 0.5h |\n108: \n109: **Deliverable:** Validator tests pass with >85% coverage.\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## ST-2.7 — Unit Tests (Middleware)\n114: \n115: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n116: |---|------|--------------|------|\n117: | 2.7.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n118: | 2.7.2 | Write `TestMiddleware_ValidToken` | Request with valid token passes to handler | 0.5h |\n119: | 2.7.3 | Write `TestMiddleware_MissingToken` | Returns 401 with correct error | 0.5h |\n120: | 2.7.4 | Write `TestMiddleware_InvalidFormat` | Returns 401 for malformed header | 0.5h |\n121: | 2.7.5 | Write `TestMiddleware_InvalidSignature` | Returns 401 for bad signature | 0.5h |\n122: | 2.7.6 | Write `TestMiddleware_ExpiredToken` | Returns 401 for expired token | 0.5h |\n123: | 2.7.7 | Write `TestMiddleware_InvalidIssuer` | Returns 403 for wrong issuer | 0.5h |\n124: | 2.7.8 | Write `TestMiddleware_ContextPropagation` | Claims available in handler context | 0.5h |\n125: \n126: **Deliverable:** Middleware tests pass.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## ST-2.8 — Integration Tests\n131: \n132: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n133: |---|------|--------------|------|\n134: | 2.8.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/integration_test.go` | File with build tag | 0.5h |\n135: | 2.8.2 | Write `TestIntegration_EndToEnd` | Full middleware flow | 0.5h |\n136: | 2.8.3 | Write test helpers for token generation | Can generate test JWTs | 0.5h |\n137: \n138: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass.\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## ST-2.9 — Documentation\n143: \n144: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n145: |---|------|--------------|------|\n146: | 2.9.1 | Add package-level GoDoc | Overview documentation | 0.5h |\n147: | 2.9.2 | Document exported types | Clear usage docs | 0.5h |\n148: | 2.9.3 | Document exported functions | Parameters and return values | 0.5h |\n149: | 2.9.4 | Add usage example | Example code in godoc | 0.5h |\n150: \n151: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## Summary\n156: \n157: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n158: |-------|-------|------------|\n159: | ST-2.1: Type Definitions | 4 | 2h |\n160: | ST-2.2: Error Definitions | 7 | 2h |\n161: | ST-2.3: Token Validation | 9 | 5h |\n162: | ST-2.4: HTTP Middleware | 6 | 3h |\n163: | ST-2.5: Configuration | 7 | 3.5h |\n164: | ST-2.6: Unit Tests (Validator) | 9 | 4.5h |\n165: | ST-2.7: Unit Tests (Middleware) | 8 | 4h |\n166: | ST-2.8: Integration Tests | 3 | 1.5h |\n167: | ST-2.9: Documentation | 4 | 2h |\n168: | **Total** | **57** | **27.5h** |\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n173: \n174: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` — Type definitions\n175: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` — Error definitions\n176: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` — JWTValidator implementation\n177: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` — HTTP middleware\n178: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` — Configuration loading\n179: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` — Validator unit tests\n180: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` — Middleware unit tests\n181: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/integration_test.go` — Integration tests\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Verification Commands\n186: \n187: ```bash\n188: # Build verification\n189: go build ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n190: \n191: # Unit tests\n192: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -v\n193: \n194: # With coverage\n195: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -cover\n196: \n197: # Race detection\n198: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -race\n199: \n200: # Integration tests\n201: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -tags=integration -v\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## Definition of Done\n207: \n208: - [ ] All 57 tasks complete\n209: - [ ] JWTValidator interface fully implemented\n210: - [ ] HTTP middleware validates tokens correctly\n211: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>85% coverage)\n212: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n213: - [ ] Race detector clean\n214: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/picod/jwt/...` succeeds\n215: - [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## Dependencies\n220: \n221: | Dependency | Purpose |\n222: |------------|---------|\n223: | AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API | Integration target |\n224: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT parsing and validation |\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Design Notes\n229: \n230: - **Algorithm preference**: RS256 for production, HS256 for simpler setups\n231: - **Token source**: HTTP Authorization header only (Bearer scheme)\n232: - **Required claims**: exp (expiration), iss (issuer)\n233: - **Clock skew**: Configurable, default 1 minute\n234: - **Context key**: Private key for claims storage in context\n235: - **Error responses**: JSON format with error/message fields\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 (PicoD JWT Middleware)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-1 (Kickoff) → ST-2 (Design)  \n> **Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-017 implements JWT authentication middleware for PicoD API endpoints. The middleware validates bearer tokens using HMAC (HS256) or RSA (RS256) signatures, with support for expiration and issuer claim validation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-2.1 — Type Definitions\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775879307683,"end":1775879307714}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879307718,"sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7b4c4001oAC2bWNmJS6uPU","messageID":"msg_d7aa79331001xlSKjBm34B1DTW","sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n10: \n11: The PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL validate JWT tokens from the Authorization header using configurable signing algorithms and claims.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Valid HS256 token passes validation\n22: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with HS256 and secret \"test-secret\"\n23: - **AND** `ValidationOptions{Algorithm: \"HS256\", Secret: []byte(\"test-secret\")}`\n24: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify the HMAC signature\n26: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Valid RS256 token passes validation\n29: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with RS256 using a private key\n30: - **AND** the corresponding public key is configured\n31: - **AND** `ValidationOptions{Algorithm: \"RS256\", PublicKey: rsaPubKey}`\n32: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify the RSA signature\n34: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns error\n37: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with invalid signature\n38: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrInvalidSignature`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Expired token returns error\n42: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with `exp` claim in the past\n43: - **AND** no clock skew configured\n44: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n45: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrTokenExpired`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Clock skew allows near-expired tokens\n48: - **GIVEN** a JWT token expired 30 seconds ago\n49: - **AND** `ClockSkew: 1m` configured\n50: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n51: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL accept the token\n52: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Wrong issuer returns error\n55: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with `iss: \"other-service\"`\n56: - **AND** `ExpectedIssuer: \"auth-service\"` configured\n57: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n58: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrInvalidIssuer`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Unsupported algorithm returns error\n61: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with ES256\n62: - **AND** `AllowedAlgorithms: [\"HS256\", \"RS256\"]` configured\n63: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n64: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm`\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ### Requirement: HTTP Middleware\n69: \n70: The system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that extracts and validates JWT tokens from requests.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Request with valid token proceeds to handler\n73: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: Bearer <valid_token>`\n74: - **AND** JWTMiddleware is configured with valid validator\n75: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n76: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL extract the token\n77: - **AND** validate it successfully\n78: - **AND** call the wrapped handler\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Request without token returns 401\n81: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request without Authorization header\n82: - **WHEN** the request is processed by JWTMiddleware\n83: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n84: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Request with invalid token format returns 401\n87: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: invalid_format`\n88: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n89: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n90: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token format\"}`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n93: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: Bearer <bad_sig_token>`\n94: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n95: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n96: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n99: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with expired JWT token\n100: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n101: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n102: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Invalid issuer returns 403\n105: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with token from wrong issuer\n106: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n107: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 403\n108: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}`\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Claims are added to request context\n111: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with claims\n112: - **AND** a request with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n113: - **WHEN** the wrapped handler is called\n114: - **THEN** the request context SHALL contain the parsed `Claims`\n115: - **AND** the handler can retrieve claims via `GetClaims(ctx)`\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: Configuration\n120: \n121: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: HS256 configuration loads secret from env\n124: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_SECRET=my-secret`\n125: - **AND** `PICOD_JWT_ALG=HS256`\n126: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n127: - **THEN** the validator SHALL use HMAC with secret \"my-secret\"\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: RS256 configuration loads public key from file\n130: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY=/path/to/key.pem`\n131: - **AND** `PICOD_JWT_ALG=RS256`\n132: - **AND** a valid RSA public key file at that path\n133: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n134: - **THEN** the validator SHALL use the loaded RSA public key\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Issuer is required configuration\n137: - **GIVEN** no `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` environment variable\n138: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n139: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error\n140: - **AND** fail fast on startup\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Clock skew configuration is parsed\n143: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW=2m`\n144: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n145: - **THEN** the validator SHALL allow 2 minutes of clock skew\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Changes to Base Specification\n150: \n151: This AR adds authentication middleware to AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API). No modifications to existing interfaces.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## New Interfaces\n156: \n157: ### JWTValidator Interface\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: package jwt\n161: \n162: import \"context\"\n163: \n164: // JWTValidator validates JWT tokens\n165: type JWTValidator interface {\n166:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n167: }\n168: \n169: // Claims represents validated JWT claims\n170: type Claims struct {\n171:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`\n172:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`\n173:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n174:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n175: }\n176: \n177: // ValidationOptions configures the validator\n178: type ValidationOptions struct {\n179:     Algorithm       string\n180:     Secret          []byte        // For HS256\n181:     PublicKey       *rsa.PublicKey // For RS256\n182:     ExpectedIssuer  string\n183:     ClockSkew       time.Duration\n184:     AllowedAlgs     []string\n185: }\n186: \n187: // NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with options\n188: func NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Middleware Function\n192: \n193: ```go\n194: // MiddlewareOptions configures the middleware behavior\n195: type MiddlewareOptions struct {\n196:     Validator    JWTValidator\n197:     ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n198: }\n199: \n200: // JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation\n201: func JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n202: \n203: // GetClaims retrieves validated claims from context\n204: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ### Error Types\n208: \n209: ```go\n210: var (\n211:     ErrMissingToken         = errors.New(\"jwt: missing bearer token\")\n212:     ErrInvalidTokenFormat   = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid token format\")\n213:     ErrInvalidSignature     = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid signature\")\n214:     ErrTokenExpired         = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n215:     ErrInvalidIssuer        = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid issuer\")\n216:     ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm = errors.New(\"jwt: unsupported algorithm\")\n217: )\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ---\n221: \n222: ## Modified Interfaces\n223: \n224: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Behavioral Changes\n229: \n230: | Behavior | Before | After |\n231: |----------|--------|-------|\n232: | API authentication | None | JWT token validation required |\n233: | Request processing | Direct | Through middleware layer |\n234: | Error responses | Application-defined | Standardized auth errors |\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## Dependencies\n239: \n240: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n241: |------------|---------|---------|\n242: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT parsing and validation |\n243: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Local | Integration with AR-015 |\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## File Index\n248: \n249: | Path | Purpose |\n250: |------|---------|\n251: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options types |\n252: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation |\n253: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware |\n254: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Configuration loading |\n255: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error definitions |\n256: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests |\n257: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Middleware tests |\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Constants\n262: \n263: | Constant | Value | Description |\n264: |----------|-------|-------------|\n265: | `defaultClockSkew` | `1m` | Default clock skew tolerance |\n266: | `authorizationHeader` | `\"Authorization\"` | HTTP header name |\n267: | `bearerPrefix` | `\"Bearer \"` | Token prefix |\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## Configuration\n272: \n273: ### Environment Variables\n274: \n275: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n276: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n277: | `PICOD_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 | - | HMAC secret for HS256 |\n278: | `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY` | RS256 | - | Path to RSA public key PEM file |\n279: | `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` | Yes | - | Expected issuer claim |\n280: | `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW` | No | `1m` | Clock skew tolerance |\n281: | `PICOD_JWT_ALG` | No | `RS256` | Signing algorithm |\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## API Endpoints Summary\n286: \n287: This AR provides middleware functionality; no new endpoints are exposed.\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Migration Notes\n292: \n293: - Add `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` dependency to go.mod\n294: - Configure JWT environment variables before deployment\n295: - Apply middleware to protected routes using `JWTMiddleware(opts)`\n296: - Existing unauthenticated endpoints remain unaffected\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n301: \n302: 1. **Token Validation**: HS256 and RS256 tokens validated correctly\n303: 2. **Claims Validation**: exp, iss claims validated with clock skew support\n304: 3. **Middleware**: HTTP middleware extracts and validates bearer tokens\n305: 4. **Error Responses**: Appropriate HTTP 401/403 responses for auth failures\n306: 5. **Configuration**: All settings configurable via environment variables\n307: 6. **Context Integration**: Parsed claims available via GetClaims(ctx)\n308: 7. **Unit Tests**: >85% coverage on validation logic\n309: 8. **Integration Tests**: End-to-end middleware flow tested\n\n(End of file - total 309 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n\nThe PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate JWT tokens from the Authorization header using configurable signing algorithms and claims.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879307691,"end":1775879307717}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879307721,"sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7bb5f001qfStcQl1qY7sDg","messageID":"msg_d7aa79331001xlSKjBm34B1DTW","sessionID":"ses_285588390ffes13MP8IEGHIZ9q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/notes.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/notes.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Notes\n2: \n3: ## Design Decisions\n4: \n5: ### Algorithm Support\n6: \n7: - Primary: RS256 (RSA with SHA-256) - recommended for production\n8: - Secondary: HS256 (HMAC with SHA-256) - for simpler deployments\n9: - Future: ES256 (ECDSA) - if needed for specific use cases\n10: \n11: ### Token Source\n12: \n13: - HTTP Authorization header with \"Bearer\" scheme\n14: - No support for query parameters (security risk)\n15: - No support for cookies (not needed for API)\n16: \n17: ### Claims Validation\n18: \n19: - Required: `exp` (expiration)\n20: - Required: `iss` (issuer)\n21: - Optional: `sub` (subject) - stored in context but not validated\n22: - Optional: `iat` (issued at) - used if present\n23: - Not validated: `aud`, `nbf` - may add if needed\n24: \n25: ### Clock Skew\n26: \n27: - Default: 1 minute tolerance\n28: - Configurable via environment\n29: - Accounts for clock drift between issuer and validator\n30: \n31: ## Open Questions\n32: \n33: 1. Should we support JWKS endpoint for automatic key rotation?\n34: 2. Do we need to validate `aud` (audience) claim?\n35: 3. Should expired tokens include refresh hints?\n36: 4. Is rate limiting needed for failed auth attempts?\n37: \n38: ## References\n39: \n40: - RFC 7519: JSON Web Token (JWT)\n41: - RFC 7515: JSON Web Signature (JWS)\n42: - RFC 7517: JSON Web Key (JWK)\n43: - AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API\n44: \n45: ## Change Log\n46: \n47: | Date | Author | Change |\n48: |------|--------|--------|\n49: | 2024-XX-XX | - | Initial scaffold creation |\n50: \n51: ## Related Documents\n52: \n53: - `/design.md` - Architecture and design details\n54: - `/plan.md` - Implementation plan\n55: - `/delta-spec.md` - API specification changes\n56: - `/tests.md` - Test specifications\n57: - `/tasks.md` - Task breakdown\n\n(End of file - total 57 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Notes\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### Algorithm Support\n\n- Primary: RS256 (RSA with SHA-256) - recommended for production\n- Secondary: HS256 (HMAC with SHA-256) - for simpler deployments\n- Future: ES256 (ECDSA) - if needed for specific use cases\n\n### Token Source\n\n- HTTP Authorization header with \"Bearer\" scheme\n- No support for query parameters (security risk)\n- No support for cookies (not needed for API)\n\n### Claims Validation\n\n- Required: `exp` (expiration)\n- Required: `iss` (issuer)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/notes.md","time":{"start":1775879307693,"end":1775879307719}}}}
